      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ear of the Beholder</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Pryor Dodge letter says adoption of digital technology for organs could results in pipe organs going way of the carillon, where a tower of bells has regrettably given way to a tower of loudspeakers (July 27 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>With the adoption of digital technology for some organs, can we now expect organs to go the way of the carillon, where a tower of bells has regrettably given way to a tower of loudspeakers?</p>
        <p>PRYOR DODGE  New York</p>
      </block>
